    "attributes": {
        "action": "Lower universal credit earnings threshold (the AET) for single parents",
        "additional_details": "Administrative earnings threshold (AET) has risen significantly over the last 3 years:\r\n2023 - \u00a3617\r\n2024 - \u00a3892\r\n2025 - \u00a3952!\r\nUniversal Credit Administrative Earnings Threshold (AET) keeps rising and so does cost of living! The cost of living is leaving many single parents struggling to make ends meet and falling into poverty.",
        "background": "Many single parents are struggling to find more hours or new jobs that work around school holidays, resulting in pressure from the job centre with weekly phone calls / meetings. It is difficult to find holiday clubs for over 5\u2019s in many areas which adds more pressure on the parent.",
